    }
  ],
  "remarks": "Alexey Dyumin has been the Presidential Aide to President of Russian Federation since 14 May 2024, and a member of the Russian Security Council since 30 September 2024. In his role as Presidential Aide, he oversees issues concerning the military-industrial complex, ensures the activities of the State Council, and the development of sports. He was Governor of the Tula Oblast 2016-2024. Previously, he led the Russian military’s Special Operations Forces, overseeing the annexation of Crimea in 2014.",
